covered: Valid and diverse retrieval scenarios including default and parameterized requests (TC01-TC07).
Empty response handling when no accounts exist (TC08) and when offset exceeds data (TC09).
Pagination behavior tested for offset/limit, boundary conditions, and large datasets (TC02, TC21, TC19, TC46, TC47-49, TC50).
Account data shaping: optional balance and CBA fields toggling (TC03, TC04, TC42).
Audit information handling with FULL and MINIMAL levels (TC05, TC06, TC07, TC33).
Error handling for invalid parameters and unsupported inputs (TC10-TC13, TC38, TC39, TC40, TC23, TC24).
Authorization handling (401) for missing or invalid credentials (TC15, TC16).
Service reliability and resilience scenarios (service down TC17, network timeout TC18, transient recovery TC36, dependency recovery TC37).
Security tests for injection and XSS (TC23, TC24).
Performance and scalability tests including large data volume (TC19) and concurrent requests (TC20).
Edge-case coverage including extra parameters ignored (TC29), invalid HTTP method (TC40), missing audit (TC45), and parameter boundary tests (TC27, TC28, TC48, TC49, TC47, TC50).
gaps: Rate limiting / throttling behavior not tested (e.g., 429 responses).
Caching behavior and headers (ETag, Cache-Control) not tested.
Authorization scenario for insufficient role (403) not covered.
Internal server error (500) scenarios not explicitly tested.
JSON schema validation of Account object payload beyond array structure not tested.
recommendations: Add rate-limiting tests (429) and test throttling.
Add tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and cache invalidation.
Add 403 Forbidden test for insufficient permissions.
Add 500 Internal Server Error scenario to ensure proper handling.
Add JSON schema validation for Account object payload.
Consider a focused, maintainable subset of edge-case parameter tests to avoid duplication.
